# Testing Guidelines

## Unit Testing
- We use standard testing frameworks (like Jest or Vitest) for our unit tests.
- Place unit tests adjacent to the file they are testing (e.g., `user.service.ts` -> `user.service.spec.ts`) or in a dedicated `__tests__` folder.
<% if (options.architecture === 'nestjs') { %>
- Utilize the `@nestjs/testing` module to create isolated testing modules.
- Mock dependencies (repositories, other services) using custom providers in the `TestingModule`.
<% } else { %>
- Mock external dependencies and database calls.
<% } %>

## E2E Testing
- Write End-to-End tests for critical API routes.
- Use `supertest` to mock HTTP requests against the application instance.
